<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[96,607,1138,1320]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
This close relative of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otto &amp; Hill" authorityYear="2017" box="[345,476,1138,1163]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Maratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis box="[345,476,1138,1163]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">M. cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a fiery or burnt-orange colour on the fan, hence the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schubert" authorityYear="2019" box="[167,285,1200,1225]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Maratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="combustus">
<emphasis box="[167,285,1200,1225]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">combustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although not shown here, males of this species also extend and display lateral opisthosomal flaps to females during courtship. Photo by Joseph Schubert.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
